e wash away of the ballast the rail require rectification before we be able to get my train over even at a foot pace each bridge also re quired elaborate examination before adventure the train upon it and eventually we be oblige to carry large baulk of tim ber to temporarily shore up many of the bridge and culvert whilst we pass over them under these circumstance it may be imagine that my prog res wa by no mean rapid and a we have frequently to halt also to replenish my supply of wood fuel we consider we have achieve wonder when on the even of the second day hour and mile out from erzeroum we finally enter the gorge of the mountain where we understand my worst trouble to lie thi be the same gorge into which the road from erzeroum to kar descend from the foot-hill to cro the frontier the railway however follow the main ara river val ley till the frontier gorge enter it whilst the road cut off the corner and join the rail again at the frontier post of zivin some mile from the main valley soon after enter the gorge we be confront by the first seriou fall of rock about ton have fall from the cliff face and entirely obliterate the railway track here therefore we halt and send my engine back prepare to david davidian dbd armenium ha not learn a lesson in center for regional study anatolium and ha forget the box punishment inflict on it cambridge ma late turkish president turgut ozal 